# 🔐 Password Strength Analyzer (Built From Scratch)

Ek Python project jo password ki security check karta hai — **entropy calculation, character variety, common-password dictionary check, aur weak pattern detection** jaise real cybersecurity concepts use karke. Koi external library (zxcvbn, password-strength) nahi — sab kuch Python standard library (`re`, `math`, `string`, `os`) se.

## 📁 Project Structure
```
password-strength-analyzer/
├── analyzer.py            # Core logic/engine (saara analysis yahan)
├── main.py                # CLI (terminal) interface
├── gui.py                 # Tkinter GUI (real-time strength meter)
├── common_passwords.txt   # Dictionary attack check ke liye wordlist
└── README.md               # Ye guide
```

---

## 🧩 Step 1: VS Code mein Setup

1. Naya folder banao: `password-strength-analyzer`
2. VS Code mein `File > Open Folder` se ye folder open karo
3. Upar di gayi 4 files (analyzer.py, main.py, gui.py, common_passwords.txt) banao
4. Terminal open karo (`` Ctrl+` ``) aur confirm karo Python installed hai:
   ```
   python --version
   ```
   (Python 3.8+ chahiye, koi extra `pip install` ki zarurat nahi — sab built-in hai)

---

## 🧠 Step 2: Concepts Samjho (interview/viva ke liye important)

| Concept | Kya hai | Is project mein kahan |
|---|---|---|
| **Entropy** | Password ki "randomness" bits mein — jitni zyada, utna mushkil brute-force karna | `calculate_entropy()` |
| **Pool Size** | Kitne mumkin characters har position par ho sakte hain (26 lower + 26 upper + 10 digit + 32 special) | `check_character_variety()` |
| **Dictionary Attack** | Hackers pehle common/leaked passwords try karte hain | `check_common_password()` |
| **Pattern Detection** | Sequential (abc, 123) ya repeated (aaa) characters kamzori hoti hain | `detect_patterns()` |
| **Crack-Time Estimate** | Entropy se andaza — attacker ko password guess karne mein kitna time lagega | `estimate_crack_time()` |

**Entropy formula:** `entropy = length × log2(pool_size)`
Simple analogy: agar password sirf lowercase (26 options) ka hai aur 8 characters lamba hai, to attacker ke paas 26⁸ combinations guess karne hain. Log2 se hum bataate hain ye "kitne bits" ke barabar mushkil hai.

---

## 🔨 Step 3: analyzer.py samjho (core engine)

Ye file **koi input/output nahi karti** — sirf functions hain jo password lete hain aur result return karte hain. Ye "separation of concerns" hai: engine ko interface (CLI/GUI) se alag rakhna, taake ek hi engine dono jagah use ho sake.

Order of logic:
1. `load_common_passwords()` — file se wordlist load karta hai
2. `check_character_variety()` — 4 types check karta hai
3. `calculate_entropy()` — bits nikalta hai
4. `detect_patterns()` — regex se weak patterns dhoondta hai
5. `check_common_password()` — dictionary mein match check
6. `length_score()` — length ke hisaab se points
7. `generate_suggestions()` — user-friendly tips banata hai
8. `analyze_password()` — sab kuch combine karke final score (0-100) aur rating deta hai

**Scoring breakdown (max 100):**
- Length → max 30 points
- 4 character types → 10 points har type = max 40
- Entropy bonus → max 30 points
- Weak pattern mile to → -10 per issue
- Common password mila to → score force ho kar ≤5 ho jata hai (kyunke wo turant crackable hai, chahe wo lamba bhi ho)

---

## 💻 Step 4: CLI Version Run Karo

Terminal mein:
```
cd password-strength-analyzer
python main.py
```
Password type karoge to screen par nazar nahi ayega (`getpass` module use hua hai — jaise real login systems karte hain). Enter dabate hi poori report print hogi: score, entropy, character breakdown, aur suggestions.

---

## 🖥 Step 5: GUI Version Run Karo (bonus, real-time meter)

```
python gui.py
```
Jaise type karoge, progress bar aur rating **live update** hoga (color bhi red se green tak change hoga). Ye `<KeyRelease>` event ke through kaam karta hai — har key chhorne par `on_key_release()` function call hota hai jo dobara analyze karta hai.

---

## ⏱ Step 5.5: Crack-Time Estimator Samjho

Ye feature entropy ko **real time** mein convert karta hai — "ye password brute-force karne mein kitna time lagega?"

**Formula:**
```
total_combinations = 2 ^ entropy_bits
average_guesses     = total_combinations / 2   (attacker average aadhe mein mil jata hai)
time                = average_guesses / attacker_speed
```

Teen alag attacker scenarios dikhaye jate hain, kyunke real duniya mein attack ki speed uske method par depend karti hai:

| Scenario | Speed | Kab hota hai |
|---|---|---|
| Online (throttled) | ~100 guesses/sec | Jab login form rate-limiting laga ke rakhe (normal websites) |
| Offline (slow hash) | ~10,000 guesses/sec | Jab database leak ho jaye lekin password bcrypt/argon2 se hashed ho |
| Offline (fast hash/GPU) | ~10 billion guesses/sec | Jab database leak ho aur password kamzor hashing (MD5/SHA1) ya bilkul plain-text se store ho |

Agar password **common list** mein already maujood hai, to crack-time "Instantly" dikhata hai — kyunke wo entropy/length ki parwah kiye baghair guess #1 par hi mil jata hai. Ye ek important lesson hai: **length aur variety kaafi nahi, agar password predictable/common hai to wo phir bhi kamzor hai.**

---

## 🧪 Step 6: Test Karo Different Passwords Ke Sath

| Password | Expected Rating | Kyun |
|---|---|---|
| `123456` | Very Weak | Common list mein hai |
| `password123` | Very Weak | Common list mein hai (chahe variety ho) |
| `aaaa1111` | Weak | Repeated pattern detect hota hai |
| `Gujrat@2024` | Strong | Decent length + variety, koi pattern nahi |
| `MyD0g!LovesPizza#99` | Very Strong | Lambi, high variety, high entropy |

---

## 🚀 Step 7: Isko Aage Kaise Le Jao (CV/Portfolio ke liye)

Ye base project hai — tum inme se koi bhi feature add kar sakte ho:
- **Crack-time estimate**: entropy se andaza lagao ke brute-force mein kitna time lagega (`2^entropy / guesses_per_second`)
- **Real leaked-password list**: `common_passwords.txt` ki jagah RockYou jaisi bari list use karo (10k-100k entries)
- **Password generator**: ek button add karo jo strong random password suggest kare
- **GitHub par upload**: is project ko apne Face Recognition aur Weather App ke sath GitHub profile mein daal do — cybersecurity-focused internships ke liye acha signal hai

---

## ⚠️ Note
Ye tool sirf **educational/analysis** ke liye hai. Real production systems mein password hashing (bcrypt/argon2) ke sath store karo, kabhi bhi plain-text mein save mat karo.